{{Infobox software | name = British Society for Plant Pathology | logo = [[Image:Bspplogo2008.jpg|150 px]] | website = http://www.bspp.org.uk }}
The '''British Society for Plant Pathology''', or '''BSPP''', is a [[UK]] based organisation of British [[phytopathology|plant pathologists]] but accepts members from all countries.<ref>http://www.bspp.org.uk/</ref> It was founded in 1981 and publishes three [[scientific journals]]: [[Plant Pathology (journal)|Plant Pathology]]<ref>https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/page/journal/13653059/homepage/productinformation.html</ref>, [[Molecular Plant Pathology]]<ref>https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/page/journal/13643703/homepage/productinformation.html</ref> and New Disease Reports.<ref>https://www.ndrs.org.uk/</ref>
The organisation actively tries to encourage its younger members to participate. Each year an award is given out each year for the best [[student]] paper published in one of societies journals. The PH Gregory prize is awarded to the best presenter of an oral paper at the annual presidential meeting.
Like other organisations of its type it arranges [[Academic conference|conference]]s and also awards various [[scholarship]]s and [[scholarship|fellowship]]s.
