[[File:Health Research Authority logo.svg|thumb|Health Research Authority logo]] The '''Health Research Authority''' ('''HRA''') is an executive [[non-departmental public body]] of the [[Department of Health (United Kingdom)|Department of Health]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref name="HRAweb" >{{cite web | url=http://www.hra.nhs.uk/ | title=Health Research Authority | accessdate= 18 April 2013}}</ref> The HRA exists to provide a unified national system for the governance of health research. The current chair of the HRA is [[Jonathan Montgomery]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hra.nhs.uk/about-the-hra/board | title= Health Research Authority |accessdate=15 April 2017}}</ref>
== History == The formation of the HRA came as a result of reorganisation of the [[National Health Service (England)|National Health Service]] (NHS) in [[England]] outlined in the [[Health and Social Care Act 2012]], and took on the functions of the National Research Ethics Service.<ref name="HRAweb" /> Originally established as a [[Special Health Authority]] on 1 December 2011, it became a [[non-departmental public body]] on 1 January 2015 under the [[Care Act 2014]].
