'''Ramsey Cottage Hospital''' is a small hospital in [[Ramsey, Isle of Man]].
Before the establishment of the Manx Health Service in 1948 it was a voluntary hospital. Medical care was provided, apart from specialist services, by the local general practitioners and paid for by a beddage fund. At that time it had a modern and well-equipped operating theatre and in the year to October 1947, 203 operations were performed.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Gellion |first1=Donald |title=Birth of a Service |date=2008 |location=Isle of Man |url=http://www.isle-of-man.com/manxnotebook/fulltext/nhs2008/ch07.htm |accessdate=31 May 2018}}</ref>
There was a Maternity Home in Ramsey, in Brookhill Road, which closed in 1947.
