'''Victoria Hospital''' is the main public health care facility in [[Saint Lucia]]. It is located in [[Castries]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Storm of century heads for Jamaica |work=The Milwaukee Journal |agency=Associated Press |date=5 August 1980 |page=3 |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=cuAjAAAAIBAJ&sjid=risEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6914,2066117&dq=victoria-hospital+castries+%7C+saint-lucia&hl=en}}</ref> The hospital opened in 1887.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Resource Sustainability And Caribbean Development |author=McGregor, Duncan ed. |author2=David Barker |author3=Sally Lloyd-Evans  |publisher=The Press, University of the West Indies |year=1998 |page=72 |isbn=978-9766400675 |url=https://books.google.com.vc/books?id=GFDLet_K5HEC&pg=PA72&lpg=PA72&dq=%22Victoria+Hospital%22+1887+Castries+OR+%22Saint+Lucia%22&source=bl&ots=Bib5Png1AU&sig=rwdTfN8H1PfIgv_RosV3THIkqqE&hl=en&sa=X&ei=C5T7T5CVJoiQ8wS_4cGIBw&sqi=2&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Victoria%20Hospital%22%201887%20Castries%20OR%20%22Saint%20Lucia%22&f=false
}}</ref>

The New National Hospital is under construction. It will replace Victoria Hospital.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.caribbean360.com/index.php/news/14339.html |title=EU, St Lucia sign hospital building contract |publisher=Caribbean 360 |date=28 January 2009 |accessdate=10 July 2012}}</ref>

